CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 3, 1959, pg. A2 reads: "F. & A.M. Widows' banquet - Star of the West Lodge, 2, F.& A.M., sponsored its annual widow's banquet at Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall, Sept. 26. Among those present were Mr. and Mrs. Major A. Greene, Anna Watkins, Mrs. Edna Ingram, Mrs. Harriet Jackson, Emmanual Phillips, D.D.G.M.; Alan Williams, W.M.; Mrs. Alan Williams, Judge Loran L. Lewis, Lee A. Harris, D.D.G.M.; Mrs. Sara Walton, H.A. Walton, D.D.G.L.; and Joseph Givens, P.G.M., M.W.P.H.G.L. of Pennsylvania. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Six men, one wearing dinner jacket, and two women, seated at long banquet table in Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall for annual Star of the West Lodge widow's banquet
